1️⃣ Offset Pagination (Traditional Way)

This is what you’ve already used:

SELECT * FROM transaction
ORDER BY created_at DESC
LIMIT 10 OFFSET 20;

Meaning:

Skip first 20 rows, return next 10 rows.

In Spring Boot:

Pageable pageable = PageRequest.of(page, size, sort);

Example:

page = 2
size = 10

DB calculates:

OFFSET = page * size = 20
✅ Advantages

Very simple

Easy to implement

Good for small datasets

Works well in admin dashboards

❌ Problems (Very Important)
1️⃣ Performance Issue (Big Tables)

If table has 10 million rows:

OFFSET 1000000

Database still scans 1 million rows internally ❌

Slow ❌
High CPU ❌
Bad for banking systems ❌

2️⃣ Data Inconsistency Problem

Imagine:

Page 1:

Tx5
Tx4
Tx3

Before user clicks page 2, new transaction comes.

Page 2:

Tx3
Tx2
Tx1

Duplicate or missing records happen ❌

This is serious in:

Banking statements

Payment history

Trading systems

🔥 2️⃣ Cursor Pagination (Senior Approach)

Also called:

Keyset Pagination

Seek Pagination

Instead of saying:

Skip 20 rows

We say:

Give me records AFTER this value
Example

Instead of:

LIMIT 10 OFFSET 20

We use:

SELECT *
FROM transaction
WHERE created_at < '2026-03-01T10:30:00'
ORDER BY created_at DESC
LIMIT 10;

We pass:

cursor = lastRecordCreatedAt
🔹 How It Works

Page 1:

GET /transactions?size=3

Response:

Tx5 (createdAt=10:05)
Tx4 (10:03)
Tx3 (10:01)

Cursor returned:

cursor = 10:01

Page 2 request:

GET /transactions?size=3&cursor=10:01

Query:

WHERE created_at < 10:01
ORDER BY created_at DESC
LIMIT 3;

Result:

Tx2
Tx1
Tx0
🔥 Why Cursor Pagination is Superior
✅ 1️⃣ Extremely Fast

Uses index efficiently:

CREATE INDEX idx_createdat ON transaction(created_at);

DB jumps directly to position using index.

No skipping millions of rows ✅

✅ 2️⃣ No Duplicate / Missing Records

New rows inserted?
No problem.

Because we move relative to last record.

✅ 3️⃣ Best for:

Banking transaction history

Infinite scroll UI

Trading systems

Social feeds

Payment gateways

🔹 Spring Boot Implementation (Cursor Style)

Repository:

List<Transaction> findTop10ByCreatedAtLessThanOrderByCreatedAtDesc(
        LocalDateTime cursor);

Controller:

@GetMapping("/transactions")
public List<Transaction> getTransactions(
        @RequestParam(required = false) LocalDateTime cursor) {

    if (cursor == null) {
        return transactionRepository
            .findTop10ByOrderByCreatedAtDesc();
    }

    return transactionRepository
        .findTop10ByCreatedAtLessThanOrderByCreatedAtDesc(cursor);
}
