What is ReBAC?

ReBAC = Relationship-Based Access Control

It means:

Access is granted based on relationships between users and resources.

Instead of:

“User has ROLE_ADMIN”

We say:

“User can access this resource because of their relationship to it.”

🔥 1️⃣ Why ReBAC Exists?

RBAC works like this:

If user has ROLE_MANAGER → allow approve loan

But what about:

User can view ONLY their own bank account
User can edit ONLY accounts assigned to them
Manager can approve ONLY loans in their branch

RBAC alone cannot handle this properly.

That’s where ReBAC comes in.

🧠 2️⃣ Simple Example

Imagine banking system:

Users:

Ravi

Priya

Branch Manager

Accounts:

Account A (belongs to Ravi)

Account B (belongs to Priya)

Rule:

User can view account IF user is owner of account

This is not role-based.

This is relationship-based:

User → OWNS → Account

Access depends on that relationship.

🔥 3️⃣ Real Definition

ReBAC determines access based on:

Relationships between entities

Graph-like connections

Context-aware authorization

It is widely used in:

Banking

Social networks

Enterprise SaaS

